# Supplementary software vocabulary for the spell-checker — patched onto
# the base en_US Hunspell dictionary, which (being SCOWL-derived) lacks
# many modern compound terms or stores them without affix flags (e.g.
# "workspace" can't pluralize). One entry per line, Hunspell syntax:
# a trailing "/S" applies the plural suffix rule (y→ies, +es, +s), so
# "workspace/S" also validates "workspaces". Lines starting with # and
# blank lines are ignored. Add words here rather than in Rust.

# compounds the base dict has only as bare (flagless) stems
workspace/S
runtime/S
username/S
metadata
timestamp/S
iterator/S

# compounds the base dict lacks entirely
namespace/S
filesystem/S
codebase/S
hostname/S
changeset/S
middleware
substring/S
whitespace
subcommand/S
subdirectory/S
lookahead/S
lookbehind/S
dropdown/S
tooltip/S
checkbox/S
dataset/S
keyframe/S
viewport/S
scrollbar/S
breakpoint/S
